10:20.170 --> 10:23.770
- Tell us about Kennedy Malloy.

10:23.780 --> 10:25.340
- I need to use the bathroom.

10:25.340 --> 10:26.740
- Answer the question.

10:26.750 --> 10:29.180
- Christ, I must have shot her!

10:29.180 --> 10:31.780
I must be a killer, right?

10:31.780 --> 10:33.150
- This is painful.

10:33.150 --> 10:34.420
- She's nearly there.

10:34.420 --> 10:36.250
- I killed Kennedy.

10:36.260 --> 10:38.160
That's what you want me
to say, right?

10:38.160 --> 10:39.420
- Help us understand what...

10:42.430 --> 10:45.430
Nagel!

10:45.430 --> 10:47.100
- Hey, hey, hey, hey! Come here!

10:47.100 --> 10:48.430
Come here.
- Ugh!

10:48.430 --> 10:50.270
- Settle down. Hey! Come here.

10:50.270 --> 10:51.800
Settle down.

10:51.800 --> 10:53.240
- We need a medic.
- No, I'm fine.

10:53.240 --> 10:55.110
- Not for you.

10:55.110 --> 10:56.510
- What?
She caught me by surprise.

10:56.510 --> 10:58.440
I'm not gonna hit a girl.
- Ugh!

11:02.520 --> 11:05.420
- Abigail was on two different
types of anti-depressants.

11:05.420 --> 11:06.880
Add a tab of ecstasy.

11:06.890 --> 11:08.450
- Thank god
stupid isn't a defense.

11:08.450 --> 11:10.220
- Peter!

11:10.220 --> 11:12.360
You forgot your phone.
- Thanks.

11:12.360 --> 11:13.890
- It was on my desk.

11:13.890 --> 11:15.890
U.S. attorney frank Harrison

11:15.900 --> 11:17.830
called about Abigail Chapman.

11:17.830 --> 11:20.200
- Great.
Who violated the girl's rights?

11:20.200 --> 11:21.930
- Spain,
or they're about to anyway.

11:21.930 --> 11:23.830
They want her back
for a retrial.

11:23.840 --> 11:25.440
- Hard to believe
a country that invented paella

11:25.440 --> 11:27.540
hasn't thought about
double jeopardy.

11:29.010 --> 11:31.780
Abigail Chapman is
an American citizen, your honor.

11:31.780 --> 11:33.780
Pursuant to article iv of
the extradition treaty

11:33.780 --> 11:35.510
between Spain and the U.S.,

11:35.520 --> 11:38.350
neither nation is required to
turn over its own nationals.

11:38.350 --> 11:40.350
- I have an affidavit from
the state department

11:40.350 --> 11:43.250
waiving article iv protection
for Ms. Chapman.

11:43.260 --> 11:45.390
Your honor,
she murdered a Spanish national.

11:45.390 --> 11:47.830
- So tell me, what's the point
of article iv then?

11:47.830 --> 11:49.960
She was tried in Spain
and acquitted, your honor.

11:49.960 --> 11:51.900
- The Spanish prosecutor
has presented new evidence,

11:51.900 --> 11:53.900
and filed for a retrial.

11:53.900 --> 11:55.900
- It shocks the conscious that
the U.S. attorney's office

11:55.900 --> 11:58.340
is willing to send
a citizen back to a system

11:58.340 --> 12:01.010
that ignores one of the rights
that we hold so fundamental.

12:01.010 --> 12:03.310
- Unfortunately,
our constitution doesn't buy her

12:03.310 --> 12:05.240
a cup of coffee in Madrid.

12:05.240 --> 12:06.580
- Can I assume your motive

12:06.580 --> 12:08.980
isn't strictly humanitarian,
Mr. stone?

12:08.980 --> 12:10.550
- Ms. Chapman is
a person of interest

12:10.550 --> 12:11.980
in the murder of a ccu student.

12:11.980 --> 12:13.920
- Where is she now?

12:13.920 --> 12:16.020
- She's currently detained at
a state psychiatric facility.

12:16.020 --> 12:17.560
It would be a violation
of basic human...

12:17.560 --> 12:19.090
- like we used to say as kids,

12:19.090 --> 12:21.930
"possession is nine tenths
of the law."

12:21.930 --> 12:25.560
You have 48 hours, Mr. stone,
to formally charge Ms. Chapman.

12:25.570 --> 12:28.030
If at that time,
charges have not been filed,

12:28.030 --> 12:30.030
I'll be forced to hand
her extradition over

12:30.040 --> 12:32.140
to the U.S. magistrate.

12:35.070 --> 12:36.540
- Peter.

12:36.540 --> 12:38.280
