- With you?
- With anyone.

29:31.290 --> 29:33.420
She and her other classmate
got into an argument

29:33.430 --> 29:36.560
over a line in "Daisy Miller."

29:36.560 --> 29:38.360
Long story short,

29:38.360 --> 29:41.430
Kennedy threw her book
at her classmate's head.

29:45.340 --> 29:46.900
- Professor hall.

29:46.910 --> 29:48.470
In your literature class,
you led a discussion

29:48.470 --> 29:50.610
on firearms and gun control,
correct?

29:50.610 --> 29:52.510
- My kids are well informed.

29:52.510 --> 29:54.340
The topic came up.

29:54.350 --> 29:57.180
- What was Kennedy's position
when the topic came up?

29:57.180 --> 29:59.380
- Kennedy was pro-gun.

29:59.380 --> 30:00.550
- And Bethany?

30:00.550 --> 30:03.190
- Anti-gun.

30:03.190 --> 30:04.920
- Is there a chance
your opinion of guns

30:04.920 --> 30:06.920
colored your opinion
of these young women?

30:06.930 --> 30:09.230
- I'm guilty.

30:09.230 --> 30:12.230
Guilty of wanting
our children...

30:12.230 --> 30:14.230
To be able to go to the park...

30:14.230 --> 30:15.970
Or the movies,
and not have to dodge bullets.

30:15.970 --> 30:19.270
- Maybe it's not guns
you oppose, but gun owners?

30:19.270 --> 30:21.270
- They are bored adolescents

30:21.270 --> 30:23.670
yearning for a bigger toy
than the kid down the block,

30:23.680 --> 30:26.140
and when they get it,
they can't help themselves.

30:26.140 --> 30:29.410
It's all about
their testosterone fueled egos.

30:29.410 --> 30:31.650
Now my job, Mr. stone,

30:31.650 --> 30:34.320
is imparting
knowledge and wisdom.

30:34.320 --> 30:36.450
What wisdom is more important

30:36.450 --> 30:39.460
than "don't buy something
that might kill your neighbor?"

30:39.460 --> 30:43.460
- And people who don't
accept your wisdom....

30:45.460 --> 30:47.600
Well...

30:47.600 --> 30:50.700
There will always be
ignorant jackasses.

30:53.540 --> 30:55.370
- Just so you know...

30:55.370 --> 30:59.210
I own a gun, sir.

30:59.210 --> 31:02.310
- Figures.

31:07.280 --> 31:09.020
- It was dark.

31:09.020 --> 31:10.650
All of the sudden,
Kennedy was there,

31:10.660 --> 31:14.560
standing with
a gun pointed at my face.

31:14.560 --> 31:16.490
I panicked.

31:16.490 --> 31:19.960
I thought I was going to die.

31:19.970 --> 31:22.270
I grabbed the gun.

31:22.270 --> 31:25.270
We struggled.
It went off.

31:25.270 --> 31:28.270
- Had you and Kennedy
ever had words before?

31:28.270 --> 31:30.540
- I never even saw her
until that night.

31:30.540 --> 31:33.640
- Thank you.

31:38.380 --> 31:40.650
- You never called
the police, did you?

31:40.650 --> 31:42.420
- No.
- Instead,

31:42.420 --> 31:45.250
you hid the gun and
continued playing the game.

31:45.260 --> 31:46.690
- I didn't know what to do.

31:46.690 --> 31:48.520
I was scared.

31:48.530 --> 31:50.530
- So scared you were willing
to let another classmate

31:50.530 --> 31:52.530
take the fall?
- Kennedy was pointing a gun.

31:52.530 --> 31:54.500
- So you assumed
she was going to kill you?

31:54.500 --> 31:55.630
- Yes!

31:55.630 --> 31:58.070
Only crazy people have guns.

31:58.070 --> 31:59.640
Look at all the mass shootings.

31:59.640 --> 32:01.500
Orlando.
San Bernardino.

32:01.510 --> 32:03.270
If I didn't try to take her gun,

32:03.270 --> 32:05.270
who knows what else
would've happened.

32:05.280 --> 32:07.540
- Did you know that 2.5 million
lives are saved each year

32:07.550 --> 32:09.450
by the use of firearms?

32:09.450 --> 32:11.350
200,000 of them are women.

32:11.350 --> 32:12.780
- It's propaganda.

32:12.780 --> 32:14.650
Just once,
I'd like one of these maniacs

32:14.650 --> 32:16.550
to shoot up an nra office.

32:16.550 --> 32:19.660
Things would change in a hurry.

32:23.760 --> 32:27.400
I shot Kennedy...

32:27.400 --> 32:30.670
And I'm really sorry...

32:30.670 --> 32:33.740
But I thought
she was going to shoot me.

32:49.820 --> 32:51.590
- Tough day?

32:51.590 --> 32:53.560
- Losing always is.

32:53.560 --> 32:56.490
- They're buying
all that self-defense crap?

32:56.490 --> 32:59.430
- Forensics says
there may have been a struggle.

32:59.430 --> 33:02.430
Kennedy's dad looks like
a paranoid gun nut

33:02.430 --> 33:05.670
who didn't want his spoiled baby
bothered by the riffraff.

33:05.670 --> 33:08.810
Her professor painted her as
a gun-toting hothead.

33:08.810 --> 33:10.810
Meanwhile,
Bethany is the scared,

33:10.810 --> 33:12.380
little Kansas farm girl

33:12.380 --> 33:13.780
who didn't know the victim,

33:13.780 --> 33:15.410
and therefore
had no motive to kill.

33:15.410 --> 33:16.680
- Wait.

33:16.680 --> 33:18.780
Bethany said
she didn't know Kennedy?

33:18.780 --> 33:21.420
- Didn't meet her
till that night.

33:21.420 --> 33:23.720
- There's a chance
Bethany's full of it.

33:23.720 --> 33:25.460
That story she gave Abigail.

33:25.460 --> 33:26.720
- About the rich girl on campus

33:26.720 --> 33:28.620
whose daddy bought her
a fur coat?

33:28.630 --> 33:31.730
- You think it's Kennedy?

33:33.130 --> 33:35.500
- I don't see how I can help.

33:35.500 --> 33:38.100
- Bethany testified
she didn't know Kennedy.

33:38.100 --> 33:40.100
You can prove she was lying.

33:40.110 --> 33:41.600
- Another courtroom...

33:41.610 --> 33:42.870
- You're not on trial this time.

33:42.870 --> 33:44.340
Just think of it as
a conversation

33:44.340 --> 33:45.510
between you and me.

33:45.510 --> 33:47.580
- What about the other lawyer?

33:47.580 --> 33:49.710
- Bethany was gonna let you take
the blame for Kennedy's murder.

33:49.710 --> 33:52.820
If we hadn't found the gun...

33:54.180 --> 33:57.750
- Have you ever put someone
away, Mr. stone...

33:57.760 --> 34:00.820
Who you weren't sure
was 100% guilty?

34:04.160 --> 34:06.430
- Yes.

34:08.600 --> 34:11.199
- Do you ever think about them?

34:11.199 --> 34:13.440
- I do.

34:14.870 --> 34:17.870
- What if I say I can't do it?

34:17.880 --> 34:21.179
- Then Kennedy's murder
may go unpunished.

34:24.620 --> 34:27.719
- It's up to you.

34:35.760 --> 34:40.760
Most people stared at me,
or whispered behind my back,

34:40.770 --> 34:42.670
but Bethany...

34:42.670 --> 34:45.940
She sat next to me
in a coffee shop one day.

34:45.940 --> 34:48.870
She thought that
we might be kindred spirits.

34:48.870 --> 34:50.670
- How so?

34:50.679 --> 34:53.679
- She said that we were both
outsiders on campus.

34:53.679 --> 34:56.679
She was from
Fontana, Kansas, and...

34:56.679 --> 34:59.620
I was from a Spanish prison.

34:59.620 --> 35:01.220
- Would you say
you became friends?

35:01.220 --> 35:02.790
- Yeah.

35:02.790 --> 35:05.190
We both lost our fathers...

35:05.190 --> 35:07.190
Although, hers died.

35:07.190 --> 35:09.190
Mine just...

35:09.190 --> 35:11.630
Ran away.

35:11.630 --> 35:15.460
But she let me read a story
she wrote about her dad.

35:15.470 --> 35:18.470
About how her life
would've been different...

35:18.470 --> 35:20.200
If he didn't die.

35:20.210 --> 35:24.210
- Can you describe the story?

35:24.210 --> 35:25.780
- He was rich,

35:25.780 --> 35:29.250
and he gave his daughter
anything she wanted.

35:29.250 --> 35:33.680
- Did Bethany base the character
on anyone she knew?

35:33.690 --> 35:36.820
- She based it
on Kennedy Malloy.

35:36.820 --> 35:40.720
- So if Bethany said in court
that she didn't know Kennedy...

35:40.730 --> 35:43.790
- she'd definitely be lying.

35:45.900 --> 35:48.000
- Thank you.

35:50.570 --> 35:53.300
- The police arrested you
for killing Kennedy.

35:53.300 --> 35:55.300
Is that right?
- Yes.

35:55.310 --> 35:57.310
- Did you ever tell them
about the story

35:57.310 --> 35:59.740
my client allegedly wrote?

35:59.740 --> 36:02.010
- No.
- Why not?

36:02.010 --> 36:05.480
- After what I went through
in Spain...

36:05.480 --> 36:07.880
I didn't know for sure
if Bethany had killed Kennedy.

36:07.890 --> 36:09.750
She was my friend.

36:09.750 --> 36:11.850
I didn't want her
to go through what I did.

36:11.860 --> 36:13.860
- When you killed
your boyfriend?

36:13.860 --> 36:15.990
- Approach, your h...
- No need, Mr. stone.

36:15.990 --> 36:17.630
You're out of line,
professor bannon.

36:17.630 --> 36:19.500
- True or false, Ms. Chapman?

36:19.500 --> 36:22.500
There's an outstanding order
of extradition against you

36:22.500 --> 36:25.030
to be returned to Spain
for retrial.

36:25.040 --> 36:26.940
True or false?

36:26.940 --> 36:30.040
True or false!
- True!

36:53.500 --> 36:56.870
- I had this history professor.

36:56.870 --> 37:00.470
He was smart.
Charismatic.

37:00.470 --> 37:01.940
He could tell you
everything about France

37:01.940 --> 37:03.840
from the first revolution
to the present.

37:03.840 --> 37:06.580
As far as I was concerned,
he walked on water.

37:06.580 --> 37:11.010
We got close...
- do I want to hear this?

37:11.020 --> 37:13.620
- "Just once,
I'd like one of these maniacs

37:13.620 --> 37:15.450
"to shoot up an nra office.

37:15.450 --> 37:16.950
Things would change in a hurry."

37:16.950 --> 37:19.960
That's Bethany on cross.

37:19.960 --> 37:22.830
Now professor hall...

37:22.830 --> 37:25.830
<i>- Gun owners
are the enemy, people.</i>

37:25.830 --> 37:28.430
<i>Just once,
I'd like one of these maniacs</i>

37:28.430 --> 37:30.000
<i>to shoot up an nra office.</i>

37:30.000 --> 37:32.000
<i>Things would change in a hurry.</i>

37:32.000 --> 37:34.000
- Verbatim.

37:34.010 --> 37:37.610
- I would have done anything
for my history professor.

37:37.610 --> 37:40.580
He's what I wished
my father would be...

37:40.580 --> 37:43.650
Bannon said he's going to call
Bethany for surrebuttal.

37:46.080 --> 37:49.390
- Just might work.
Smart.

37:51.090 --> 37:52.920
- Yes, I wrote the story,

37:52.920 --> 37:55.590
but I honestly don't know
how Abigail got it.

37:55.590 --> 37:57.590
- Why's that?

37:57.600 --> 37:59.560
- Abigail was odd.

37:59.560 --> 38:02.130
I don't even remember
ever talking to her.

38:02.130 --> 38:05.130
- So your story
wasn't about Kennedy?

38:05.140 --> 38:07.870
- No. It was a fantasy,

38:07.870 --> 38:10.970
about what my life would be
like if dad had lived.

38:21.120 --> 38:25.590
- This is the story
in question, is it not?

38:25.590 --> 38:27.160
- It is.

38:27.160 --> 38:28.620
- Please read
those last few lines.

38:28.630 --> 38:30.690
They're highlighted.

38:33.700 --> 38:37.700
- "But dad is gone,
and this was all a dream.

38:37.700 --> 38:40.440
"But sometimes, dreams are
right there in front of us,

38:40.440 --> 38:44.440
and all we have to do
is reach out and touch them."

38:44.440 --> 38:47.440
- That's very beautiful.
I'm...

38:47.450 --> 38:49.150
I'm surprised
you never shared it to anyone.

38:49.150 --> 38:50.980
- I might have.

38:50.980 --> 38:52.520
- Who would that be?

38:52.520 --> 38:54.150
- Not Abigail Chapman,
that's for sure.

38:54.150 --> 38:56.150
- Professor hall?

38:56.150 --> 38:58.620
He said you were one of
his best students.

38:58.620 --> 39:00.190
- Yes, I showed it to him.

39:00.190 --> 39:02.660
- What did he say?

39:02.660 --> 39:04.590
- He liked it.

39:04.600 --> 39:06.430
He said I could be a writer.

39:06.430 --> 39:07.660
Said he would help.

39:07.670 --> 39:09.970
- Did he help you?
- Yes.

39:09.970 --> 39:11.770
- After class?

39:11.770 --> 39:14.770
- Sometimes, but it's not
what you're suggesting.

39:14.770 --> 39:16.710
He was my teacher.
That's all.

39:16.710 --> 39:18.810
- Your favorite teacher?
- Yes.

39:20.640 --> 39:22.650
- He read your stories.

39:22.650 --> 39:25.650
He knew what was going on
in your head.

39:25.650 --> 39:27.650
In your heart.

39:27.650 --> 39:31.020
He knew you like
a father knows his daughter.

39:31.020 --> 39:33.620
Your dream, the one that was
standing right in front of you,

39:33.620 --> 39:35.060
close enough for you to touch?

39:35.060 --> 39:36.530
- Objection!

39:36.530 --> 39:38.090
Mr. stone is testifying,
your honor.

39:38.100 --> 39:40.100
- Sustained.
- Professor hall was that dream!

39:40.100 --> 39:41.630
- Your honor!
- He was the closest thing

39:41.630 --> 39:44.730
to a dad you ever had.
Isn't that right?

39:49.540 --> 39:51.570
- I don't know.

39:51.580 --> 39:53.580
- What would you do
if he left the school?

39:53.580 --> 39:56.110
- He won't leave.
He has tenure.

39:56.110 --> 39:58.110
- But let's say the audio
recording that Kennedy had

39:58.120 --> 40:00.580
of professor hall ranting
about the evils of guns

40:00.590 --> 40:02.250
got out to cable news?

40:02.250 --> 40:04.190
I'm sure the trustees
wouldn't like that at all,

40:04.190 --> 40:06.520
and professor hall's tenure
would be worthless, wouldn't it?

40:06.520 --> 40:07.590
And there goes your dream.

40:07.590 --> 40:09.230
Just like that.

40:09.230 --> 40:11.230
You couldn't let Kennedy
destroy your dream, could you?

40:11.230 --> 40:13.830
- I tried to talk to Kennedy...

40:13.830 --> 40:16.270
But she wouldn't leave
professor hall alone.

40:16.270 --> 40:19.740
That bitch's father
gave her everything!

40:19.740 --> 40:22.810
Why did she want
to take mine away?

40:43.830 --> 40:47.600
- In the case of the people of
Illinois vs. Bethany pierson,

40:47.600 --> 40:49.230
on the sole count of
the indictment,

40:49.230 --> 40:50.800
first degree murder,

40:50.800 --> 40:52.700
the people find the defendant...

40:52.700 --> 40:54.140
Guilty.

41:08.150 --> 41:10.150
- Huh.

41:10.150 --> 41:13.890
I remember
Gail's first year in college.

41:13.890 --> 41:15.790
She came home and yelled at me

41:15.790 --> 41:19.090
for taking part
in an illegal war.

41:19.100 --> 41:22.100
Some hippie,
draft dodger professor

41:22.100 --> 41:24.230
taught her I was the enemy.

41:24.240 --> 41:28.670
- I yelled at my parents for
wiping out the native Americans.

41:28.670 --> 41:31.740
- When did people start
going to college to get stupid?

41:34.810 --> 41:38.710
- We would've lost the case
without her, mark...

41:38.720 --> 41:40.720
- You think I'm the enemy, too?

41:40.720 --> 41:43.620
- I think you're a hero.

41:43.620 --> 41:46.620
- You're full of...

41:46.620 --> 41:49.760
Get me the damn
secretary of state.

41:49.760 --> 41:51.590
What's the girl's name?
Abigail...

41:51.600 --> 41:53.600
- Chapman.

41:53.600 --> 41:55.700
Thank you.
